The paper deals with complexity classes and algorithmic techniques for online problems with advice, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of computational complexity (cs.CC), algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on weighted versions of problems suggests a stronger connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), but the use of advice and the study of complexity classes also make cs.CC and cs.AI likely categories.
